#: 007a6:8
msgid "If I was with Haruka, I bet the time would fly right by."
msgstr "Me gustaría hablar con Haruka."

#: 007a6:9
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I wonder where she is?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Me pregunto dónde estará...\""

#: 007a6:10
msgid "I looked around the campus, and found her talking to the principal."
msgstr "Miré por ahí y la encontré hablando con la directora."

#: 007a6:11
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"She's with the principal. I shouldn't bother them.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Está con la directora. No debería molestarles.\""

#: 007a6:12
msgid "But then she saw me."
msgstr "Pero me vio."

#: 007a6:17
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Ah!\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¡¡...!!\""

#: 007a6:18
msgid "We made eye contact."
msgstr "Hubo contacto visual."

#: 007a6:21
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Hey, Kazushi-kun!\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Anda, ¡Kazushi!\""

#: 007a6:22
msgid "She started jumping up and down and waving at me. She's always energetic."
msgstr "Daba saltitos mientras agitaba el brazo saludándome."

#: 007a6:23
msgid "She gave me a big smile as I waved back at her."
msgstr "Me ofreció una radiante sonrisa cuando le devolví el saludo."

#: 007a6:26
msgid ""
"{Principal}\n"
"\"Oh, is he your friend?\""
msgstr ""
"{Directora}\n"
"\"¿Amigo tuyo?\""

#: 007a6:29
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Yes, he is. See...\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Él es...\""

#: 007a6:32
msgid "Haruka whispered something to the principal."
msgstr "Haruka susurró algo a la directora."

#: 007a6:33
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Hi......\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Hola...\""

#: 007a6:36
msgid "I knew she wasn't able to hear me, but I bowed to her anyways. The principal put on an elegant smile, said something to Haruka, and urged her towards me."
msgstr ""

#: 007a6:39
msgid "Haruka made her way through the crowd towards me."
msgstr "Haruka andó hacia mí."

#: 007a6:42
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Hah, I finally made it. There're so many people here!\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Hay demasiada gente.\""

#: 007a6:43
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Is it OK to leave her alone?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿No pasa nada por dejarla sola?\""

#: 007a6:44
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Yes, she'll be fine. She told me to come join you.\""
msgstr ""

#: 007a6:45
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Really?\n"
"The Principal did?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿En serio?\n"
"¿La directora?\""

#: 007a6:48
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"I think my grandma likes you.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Creo que le gustas a mi abuelita.\""

#: 007a6:49
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Huh? How could she?\n"
"I've hardly ever spoken to her. She shouldn't even know me.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿Sí?\n"
"Pero si apenas he hablado con ella.\""

#: 007a6:52
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Doesn't seem that way. Grandma sure remembers you from something.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¿En serio? Pues parece haberte recordado.\""

#: 007a6:53
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Seriously? So she's already keeping an eye on me, huh? ......Wait a minute?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿En serio? Quizá me recuerde por las cosas malas que habrá oído de mí.\n"
"¿Un momento...?\""

#: 007a6:54
msgid "Haruka is calling her \"grandma\" in front of me."
msgstr "Haruka la está llamando \"abuelita\" delante de mí."

#: 007a6:55
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"So she's 'grandma' today?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Hoy la estás llamando \"abuelita\".\""

#: 007a6:58
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Oh, did I say 'grandma'?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¿En serio?\""

#: 007a6:59
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"You didn't notice?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿No te habías dado cuenta?\""

#: 007a6:62
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"She gets mad at me if I don't call her 'Principal' at school. I try my best to be careful, but this mouth of mine...\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Intento con todas mis fuerzas no llamarla así en la escuela.\""

#: 007a6:63
msgid "She pinched her lips. I guess Haruka calls the principal 'grandma' outside of school."
msgstr "Se muerde los labios."

#: 007a6:64
msgid "I'm sure it's only natural for them, but the idea seemed charming to me."
msgstr "Me da un poco de lástima que tenga que distanciarse de la directora en la escuela."

#: 007a6:65
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I bet you can get away with it today. It is a party, and we do have alcohol.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"No creo que pase nada por llamarla \"abuelita\" hoy, teniendo en cuenta que estamos en una fiesta.\""

#: 007a6:68
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Oh, that's true. So you drink, Kazushi-kun? Maybe I should have one with you.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Es cierto.\n"
"¿Quieres beber conmigo?\""

#: 007a6:69
msgid "She was drinking orange juice."
msgstr "Estaba bebiendo un zumo de naranja."

#: 007a6:70
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Okay, then here you go.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Claro.\""

#: 007a6:72
# Hay que ver si realmente es una bebida alcoholica, o en la traducción al inglés
# lo cambiaron para que pareciesen más "adultos".
msgid "I brought her an empty glass and poured some liquor into it."
msgstr "Le traje un vaso vacío y vertí una bebida alcoholica en él."

#: 007a6:75
# Quizá convenga mantener la obscenidad en la frase.
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Wow!\n"
"I'm having a man pour me a drink. Does this make me a delinquent?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Guau...\n"
"Me siento especial de que un hombre esté virtiendo una bebida en mi vaso.\""

#: 007a6:77
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"A delinquent...?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Te sientes especial...\""

#: 007a6:80
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"This is romantic.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Es romántico.\""

#: 007a6:81
msgid "She's already in a good mood and she hasn't even had a sip yet! What a strange girl."
msgstr ""

#: 007a6:84
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Oh, maybe Grandma would be happy if you poured her one too?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Mi abuelita se alegraría si le llevases una bebida.\""

#: 007a6:85
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Me? Pour one for the principal?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿Yo? ¿Llevándole alcohol a la directora?\""

#: 007a6:86
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Sure! Follow me!\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¡Claro, sígueme!\""

#: 007a6:87
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"H...Hey...!\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"O-Oye...\""

#: 007a6:89
msgid "She started dragging me towards the principal before I had a chance to reply."
msgstr "Me está tirando hasta la directora antes de que me diese tiempo a replicar."

#: 007a6:94
msgid ""
"{Principal}\n"
"\"Oh, hello. What's the matter?\""
msgstr ""
"{Directora}\n"
"\"Hola a los dos.\""

#: 007a6:95
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Kazushi-kun said he'll pour you a drink!\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¡Kazushi te vertirá una bebida!\""

#: 007a6:98
# He añadido el Kazushi porque luego hace referencia a que ha recordado su nombre.
# Hay que ver si lo menciona en esta frase o en la anterior.
msgid ""
"{Principal}\n"
"\"You will, Haruma-kun?\""
msgstr ""
"{Directora}\n"
"\"¿Lo harás, Kazushi?\""

#: 007a6:99
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Su-, uh, yes...\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Sí...\""

#: 007a6:100
msgid ""
"She already remembered my name.\n"
"She had a kind, graceful smile, but something felt wrong."
msgstr "Se ha acordado de mi nombre."

#: 007a6:103
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Here, Kazushi-kun!\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¡Toma, Kazushi!\""

#: 007a6:104
# ¿Copa o vaso?
msgid "Haruka handed me an empty glass and a bottle of liquor. I prepared for the worst and handed the glass to the Principal."
msgstr "Haruka me da una copa vacía y una botella de licor."

#: 007a6:105
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Here you go, ma'am.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Aquí tiene.\""

#: 007a6:108
msgid ""
"{Principal}\n"
"\"Why, thank you very much.\""
msgstr ""
"{Directora}\n"
"\"Muchas gracias.\""

#: 007a6:110
msgid "I was nervous as I tried to pour it without spilling any. I glanced up and saw the Principal blushing like a young girl."
msgstr "Se lo vertí en la copa tratando de no derramarlo."

#: 007a6:113
msgid ""
"{Principal}\n"
"\"I feel so embarrassed. You remind me of him.\""
msgstr ""
"{Directora}\n"
"\"Me has recordado a él.\""

#: 007a6:115
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Him?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿\"Él\"?\""

#: 007a6:118
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"My grandpa.\n"
"He passed away a long time ago.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Mi abuelito.\n"
"Falleció hace mucho tiempo.\""

#: 007a6:119
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Oh. I'm sorry...\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Lo siento...\""

#: 007a6:120
msgid "So the principal is a widow. I guess they did mention that there weren't any male teachers at this academy."
msgstr "La directora es viuda."

#: 007a6:121
msgid "I wish I knew what to say at times like these."
msgstr "No sabía qué decir."

#: 007a6:124
msgid ""
"{Principal}\n"
"\"Don't trouble yourself. It happened many long years ago.\""
msgstr ""
"{Directora}\n"
"\"Ha pasado ya mucho tiempo.\""

#: 007a6:125
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"I never knew my grandpa either. He passed away before I was born.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Falleció antes de que yo naciera.\""

#: 007a6:126
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I see. In my case, I never knew my grandma.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Ya veo. Bueno, mi abuela también falleció antes de que no naciera.\""

#: 007a6:127
msgid "My grandma was already gone by the time I was born. I heard that she had died from an illness when she was young."
msgstr "Escuché que murió jóven."

#: 007a6:128
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"My grandpa used to talk about her all the time.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Mi abuelo solía hablar de ella todo el tiempo.\""

#: 007a6:131
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"It's the same in my family!\n"
"Grandma talks about grandpa all the time!\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Lo mismo pasa en mi familia\n"
"La abuelita hablaba del abuelito todo el tiempo.\""

#: 007a6:132
msgid ""
"{Principal}\n"
"\"Haruka,\n"
"you need to call me \"Principal\" here.\""
msgstr ""
"{Principal}\n"
"\"Haruka,\n"
"aquí tienes que llamarme \"directora\".\""

#: 007a6:135
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Oh, shoot! See?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¡Ups!\""

#: 007a6:138
msgid "Haruka winked at me. We had just talked about it, but the principal was slightly confused."
msgstr "Los ojos de Haruka me transmiten un \"¿ves?\"."

#: 007a6:139
msgid ""
"{Principal}\n"
"\"It looks like you're getting along well with Haruma-kun. I'm glad you've made a good friend.\""
msgstr ""
"{Directora}\n"
"\"Haruka, me alegra de que hayas hecho un buen amigo como él.\""

#: 007a6:140
msgid "When she said that, the principal's face went back to being grandma."
msgstr "Tras decir eso, su cara vuelve a ser la de la \"abuelita\"."

#: 007a6:143
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"I wasn't sure if I'd be able to get along with the boys, but luckily there are those like Kazushi-kun.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"A decir verdad, no tenía claro que fuese a llevarme bien con vosotros, chicos. Estoy muy contenta.\""

#: 007a6:144
msgid "Putting it that way made me blush. The principal watched us with the proud smile of a grandmother."
msgstr "La directora mira a Haruka orgullosa."

#: 007a6:147
msgid ""
"{Principal}\n"
"\"Well, I better be going now. Thank you very much for the drink, Haruma-kun. You've made me feel young again.\""
msgstr ""
"{Directora}\n"
"\"Tengo que marcharme. Muchas gracias por la bebida, Kazushi.\""

#: 007a6:148
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"You're welcome.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"De nada.\""

#: 007a6:151
msgid "After giving us another graceful smile, she finally left. The tension finally drained from my shoulders."
msgstr ""

#: 007a6:154
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"She seemed really happy. Thank you.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Parecía realmente contenta. Muchas gracias, Kazushi.\""

#: 007a6:155
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"No, don't mention it. All I did was pour a drink. Anyways, your grandma looks pretty young.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Tu abuela es realmente jóven.\""

#: 007a6:156
# Revisar.
msgid "I didn't know how old she was, but her skin was still radiant."
msgstr "No sé cuantos años tendrá, pero su piel sigue radiante."

#: 007a6:159
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"It's just because you talked to her, Kazushi-kun. She said you made her feel young.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Debe sentirse rejuvenecida hablando contigo.\""

#: 007a6:160
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Really?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿En serio?\""

#: 007a6:161
# Revisar.
msgid "Did she just drain my youth?"
msgstr "¿La he rejuvenecido yo?"

#: 007a6:164
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Grandma is still in love with grandpa.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"La abuelita sigue enamorada de mi abuelo.\""

#: 007a6:165
msgid "I thought I heard the tone of her voice drop, and I looked over to find a sad smile on her face."
msgstr "Por algún motivo, he notado un tono de tristeza en su voz."

#: 007a6:166
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Hey, Kazushi-kun.\n"
"What would you do if your lover died?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Oye Kazushi,\n"
"¿qué harías tú si tu amada falleciese?\""

#: 007a6:167
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"If my lover died?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿Si mi amada falleciese?\""

#: 007a6:168
# Revisar.
msgid "That was a rather serious question all of a sudden."
msgstr "Es una pregunta muy seria para ser así de sopetón..."

#: 007a6:169
msgid "I didn't know why she asked, nor how to answer."
msgstr "No sé qué decir."

#: 007a6:172
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"I'm sorry. Was that a weird question?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Lo siento. Era una pregunta muy rara.\""

#: 007a6:173
# Revisar.
msgid "She noticed I was having trouble answering, so she tried to play it off with a smile."
msgstr "Le di pena por no saber qué decir."

#: 007a6:174
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"It's OK, but why did you ask?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿Por qué me has preguntado eso?\""

#: 007a6:177
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Well, sometimes when I look at grandma, I think about how she can't forget about grandpa. I'm sure she's lonely.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Me entristece pensar en lo sola que debe sentirse mi abuelita a veces.\""

#: 007a6:180
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"I've been told that they struggled so much to get married.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"He oído que lucharon mucho para poder casarse.\""

#: 007a6:181
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"The principal did? Wow, I didn't know...\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Ya veo...\""

#: 007a6:182
msgid "It was hard to imagine that from the strict image the principal had now."
msgstr "Resulta difícil de imaginarlo viendo a la directora ahora."

#: 007a6:183
msgid "But I guess it's not surprising. They say she was really pretty when she was young. Such a romance would only be natural for her."
msgstr "Todo el mundo ha tenido romances de jóven."

#: 007a6:186
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"But, grandpa died in an accident only a year after they got married.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Pero el abuelo murió solo un año después de que se casaran.\""

#: 007a6:187
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"That soon?\n"
"That is sad... She's been alone ever since?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Tan pronto...\n"
"¿Ha estado sola desde entonces?\""

#: 007a6:190
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Yes, she has. I'm sure she's never been able to forget about him.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Supongo que es incapaz de olvidarle.\""

#: 007a6:191
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I see.\n"
"She must have really loved him.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Ya veo...\n"
"Debió quererle mucho.\""

#: 007a6:194
# Revisar.
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"She did.\n"
"I dream about being in a relationship like that.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Sí.\n"
"Yo sueño con tener una relación como la suya.\""

#: 007a6:195
# "que sueña con acabar con un príncipe azul."
msgid "She looked little girl in love with romance as she told me about her sweet dream. Haruka in love, huh? I wonder what kind of guy she likes."
msgstr "Parecía como una chiquilla que sueña con tener un tierno romance."

#: 007a6:196
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Have you ever fallen in love with somebody?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿Te has enamorado alguna vez de alguien?\""

#: 007a6:199
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"What?! Of course not!\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¿Qué? ¡Pues claro que no!\""

#: 007a6:200
msgid "She shook her head in surprise."
msgstr "Parecía muy sorprendida."

#: 007a6:201
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Never?\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"¿Nunca?\""

#: 007a6:202
# Me resulta -> ¿Me resulta"ba"? ¿pasado? Quizá no le gustaría recalcar que ahora sí.
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"There aren't any boys my age on this island. How could I have met or fallen in love with anyone?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Como puedes ver. Me resulta un pelín difícil conocer a chicos en esta isla.\""

#: 007a6:203
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Well, I suppose that's true...\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Es verdad...\""

#: 007a6:204
msgid "Of course, there weren't any boys likely to have gone after Haruka before."
msgstr "A las chicas les resulta difícil encontrarse chicos por aquí de la misma edad en la isla."

#: 007a6:207
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"I always worried I might grow old without ever getting to fall in love. Hey, Kazushi-kun, have you ever been in love?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¿Y tú? ¿Te has enamorado alguna vez de alguien?\""

#: 007a6:208
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Only as much as everyone else.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Sí. Como cualquier otro chico.\""

#: 007a6:211
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Wow, how nice. People our age should already be in love, shouldn't they? Hah...\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Tienes razón... La gente de nuestra edad debería haber tenido ya alguna experiencia de ese tipo.\""

#: 007a6:212
msgid "She heaved a deep sigh. I kind of felt bad for her."
msgstr "Exhala un largo suspiro."

#: 007a6:215
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"So, what's it like to fall in love?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Y... ¿Cómo se siente al enamorarse?\""

#: 007a6:216
msgid "She leaned forward as she asked me. Her eyes were sparkling. She was so innocent."
msgstr "Sus ojos me dicen que está desesperada por oírlo."

#: 007a6:217
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"It's like......\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Es como...\""

#: 007a6:221
msgid "I recalled a few of my previous encounters. There was the time I got slapped hard as the sun set on the park, the time one girl called me a pervert and stepped on me..."
msgstr "La verdad es que todos mis recuerdos acabaron fatal..."

#: 007a6:225
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Huh? Why are you crying?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¿Por qué estás llorando?\""

#: 007a6:226
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"All my heartbreaking memories...\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Recuerdos...\""

#: 007a6:229
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"I see. Love is so touching it brings tears.\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Ya veo. Es muy bonito.\""

#: 007a6:230
msgid "She missed the real meaning behind my words, and looked up the sky with glittering eyes."
msgstr "Me ha malentendido por completo."

#: 007a6:231
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"I want to fall in love too. I wonder how I can make that happen?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"A mí también me gustaría enamorarme.\""

#: 007a6:232
msgid "She looked just like a dreamy-eyed girl. She looked so pure and bright that I wanted to cheer her on."
msgstr "Es como una niña pequeña. Es tan pura..."

#: 007a6:233
msgid ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"I hope that one day you'll have a romance just like your grandparents had. You have my support.\""
msgstr ""
"{Kazushi}\n"
"\"Espero que algún día puedas tener un romance como el que tuvieron tus abuelos.\""

#: 007a6:236
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Really? Thank you!\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Gracias\""

#: 007a6:237
msgid "She happily took my hand in hers. Her hands felt so soft. Their warmth ran through me like a bolt of electricity."
msgstr "Me sujeta de la mano. Sus manos son tan suaves."

#: 007a6:238
msgid "Oh, no. I think I'm falling in love."
msgstr "Maldición. Creo que me estoy enamorando."

#: 007a6:241
msgid ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"Love, huh? It's so nice. I wonder how I can start a relationship?\""
msgstr ""
"{Haruka}\n"
"\"¿Cómo se puede empezar un romance?\""

#: 007a6:242
msgid "My loves had been too simple. They all led to terrible things too. I need to be a bit more prudent."
msgstr "Creo que está preguntando a la persona equivocada. Mi última relación empezó de una forma muy fácil."
